### Explanation:
The Collatz sequence is an iterative sequence defined by the following recurrence relation:

$$
\begin{align}

\begin{array}{lcl}

c_{n + 1} &= \begin{cases} 
\frac{c_{n}}{2} & \text{if $c_{n}$ is even}\\
3 c_{n} + 1 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}

\end{array}

\end{align}
$$

It can be proven that this sequence is either bounded or that it reaches a constant $1$ for any positive integer $n$.

